---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Accordion · Porchlight">
  <h1>Accordion</h1>
  <p>
    A collapsible disclosure built on native <code>&lt;details&gt;</code>/
    <code>&lt;summary&gt;</code>. Animates open/close to/from
    <code>height: auto</code> using <code>interpolate-size</code>, with a
    <code>grid-template-rows: 0fr to 1fr</code> universal fallback.
  </p>

  <h2>Multiple open (default)</h2>
  <div class="pl-c-accordion">
    <details class="pl-c-accordion__item">
      <summary class="pl-c-accordion__header">
        <span>What is Porchlight?</span>
        <svg class="pl-c-accordion__icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" /></svg>
      </summary>
      <div class="pl-c-accordion__panel">
        <div class="pl-c-accordion__content">
          Porchlight is a no-dependency, native-CSS framework. It ships as a
          single stylesheet with tokens, themes, layout, and components.
        </div>
      </div>
    </details>

    <details class="pl-c-accordion__item">
      <summary class="pl-c-accordion__header">
        <span>Does it use JavaScript?</span>
        <svg class="pl-c-accordion__icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" /></svg>
      </summary>
      <div class="pl-c-accordion__panel">
        <div class="pl-c-accordion__content">
          No. The framework ships zero JavaScript. All interactivity is native
          HTML (details, popover, dialog) or CSS-driven.
        </div>
      </div>
    </details>

    <details class="pl-c-accordion__item">
      <summary class="pl-c-accordion__header">
        <span>What browsers are supported?</span>
        <svg class="pl-c-accordion__icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" /></svg>
      </summary>
      <div class="pl-c-accordion__panel">
        <div class="pl-c-accordion__content">
          Baseline 2025+ browsers. Core features work everywhere; advanced
          features are gated behind <code>@supports</code>.
        </div>
      </div>
    </details>
  </div>

  <h2>Open by default</h2>
  <div class="pl-c-accordion" style="margin-block-start: var(--pl-space-4);">
    <details class="pl-c-accordion__item" open>
      <summary class="pl-c-accordion__header">
        <span>This item starts open</span>
        <svg class="pl-c-accordion__icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" /></svg>
      </summary>
      <div class="pl-c-accordion__panel">
        <div class="pl-c-accordion__content">
          Add the <code>open</code> attribute to <code>&lt;details&gt;</code> to
          start expanded.
        </div>
      </div>
    </details>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
